  "prompt": "Will 8 RAC tickets that have changed to CNF, get adjacent berths?",
  "response": "Whether 8 RAC tickets that have changed to CNF will get adjacent berths depends on several factors, including the availability of berths and the allocation policies of the railway system. Typically, the railway reservation system tries to allocate berths close to each other when people are traveling together, especially if they have booked under the same PNR (Passenger Name Record). However, it is not guaranteed, especially when dealing with a high number of passengers or peak travel seasons. You can check your ticket's final allocation to see the exact berths that you have received.",
